President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Steven D. Grimberg of Georgia as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Georgia. Grimberg is currently the Managing Director and General Counsel of Nardello & Co. in Atlanta, Georgia. He has previously worked as an Assistant United States Attorney and Deputy Chief of the Economic Crimes Section in the United States Attorney's Office for the Northern District of Georgia, as well as a Trial Attorney in the Department of Justice's Tax Division. Grimberg also serves as an Adjunct Professor at Emory University School of Law.

Frank W. Volk of West Virginia has been nominated to serve as a District Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of West Virginia. Volk is currently the Chief Judge of the United States Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of West Virginia. Prior to his appointment to the bench, he served as a career law clerk on the United States District Court for the Southern District of West Virginia. Volk has also been an Adjunct Professor at the West Virginia University College of Law. He received his J.D. from the West Virginia University College of Law.

Randall P. Huff of Wyoming has been nominated to serve as United States Marshal for the District of Wyoming. Huff currently works as the IT Services Field Manager for the State of Wyoming's Department of Enterprise Technology, providing technical support to law enforcement agencies. He has also worked with TLO, LLC, providing expertise on cyber-criminal investigations involving child exploitation. Huff has served as a Special Agent with the Wyoming Division of Criminal Investigations and as a member of the Torrington Police Department. He received his B.S. from the University of Wyoming and served in the United States Marine Corps.